deck_name: Legacy of the Worthless - Redeeming my Nordic Deck
deck_description: I've always regretted my deck choices for my Nordic deck in the Legacy of the Worthless YouTube series, losing to Genex in the finals. I've run it back and updated the list using my knowledge and skills now, following the banlist for the event. No more relying on BLS, and no more BS; just gas, baby.

This is an idea I came up with after looking at another decklist on here (Scrap Gizmek Barrier Deck) which focused on using the Scrap Engine to send Gizmeks to the grave to help cheat out barrier statues of any attribute. I wanted to make it where I could bring out rescue ferret, but the gizmeks can't summon it so I wanted to make a work around and this is what came of it. Combo is listed below, but a side note: Ground Xeno, one of the new cards from the Transcendrake cards, can be used as another Raptor Searcher. Jet Synchron can also be used as another extender and a way to get O-lion or Rosenix out of your hand, and a third Hero Kid can be used to help protect the combo from bricking, as well as a third Golem. 

This does NOT include whatever Rescue Ferret Combo you chose to do, but remember that you are summoning Saryuja RIGHT BEFORE triggering Ferret, so you can shuffle any bricks from said combo back into the deck. 

In Hand: Scrap Raptor/Ground Xeno/Fossil Dig/Scrapyard + Terraforming/Scrap Factory/Scrap Recycler

 

Step 0: Activate Ground Xeno/Fossil Dig/Scrapyard, Search Scrap Raptor

Step 0: Activate Terraforming, Search Scrap Factory

Step 1: Normal Summon Raptor

Step 2: Activate Raptor 1st Effect, Destroying Raptor

Step 3: Activate Raptor 2nd Effect, Search Scrap Recycler/Scrap Factory (whichever is missing)

Step 4: Activate Factory

Step 5: Normal Summon Recycler

Step 6: Activate Recycler, Send Mecha Phantom Beast O-Lion from Deck to GY

Step 7: Activate O-Lion, SS Token

Step 8: Link Summon Scrap Wyvern, using Recycler and Token

Step 9: Activate Wyvern, Reviving Recyler, then Destroying Recycler

Step 10: C1 Wyvern, C2 Factory. Factory SS Scrap Golem A, Wyvern SS Scrap Golem B, then Destroying

Factory

Step 11: Golem A Revives Recycler

Step 12: Recycler sends Rosenix

Step 13: Activate Rosenix, Banishing itself to SS Token

Step 14: Link Summon Donner, Dagger Fur Hire, using Wyvern and Token

Step 15: Link Summon Codebreaker Virus Swordsman, using Golem A and Recycler

Step 16: Activate Swordsman, SS Codebreaker Zero Day

Step 17: Link Summon Isolde, Two Tales of the Noble Knights, using Swordsman and Zero Day

Step 18: Activate Isolde 2nd Effect, sending 2 Equips to SS Hero Kid

Step 19: Activate Hero Kid effect, SS 1 Hero Kids

Step 20: Xyz Summon Number 29: Mannequin Cat, using 2 Hero Kid

Step 21: Activate Golem B, SS Recycler/Raptor to opponent's field

Step 22: Activate Number 29, SS Rescue Ferret

Step 23: Link Summon Saryuja Skull Dread, using Donner, Isolde, Number 29, and Golem B

 

Hrd Brick: Golem, Rosenix, O-lion, Hero Kid

Soft Brick: Zero Day, Ferret

deck_excerpt: personal pile deck with a dozen engines
deck_description:
;  w ; Compared to the rest, this deck is closer to a personal deck. It has my heart and soul in it and I hope you'll enjoy it!

The most important thing about the deck is seeing Kuribohs as the Glue to your deck. Get out literally any two monsters (and there's plenty of ways to do so, like with Flute of Summoning Kuriboh, the Kuribohs that summon allies to the field, or the number of self-summoners) and bring out Verte Anaconda. Aleister is fantastic at reusing spent mons in the graveyard (like when your Wandering Gryphon eventually kicks it), or Hasty Horses. Also, Destiny Dasher can also just randomly bring out a full power Parallel eXceed? Not too helpful but can work

Tbh, I kinda made like a Yugioh protag's. It has synergies and combos with jank but highly synergestic cards =  w = 

 

Main strats:

- (Hasty Horse / Invoked Raidjin) -> 5 Star Twilight -> the 5 kuribuddies

with 5 kuribohs on the board you can pretty much do WHATEVER you want. you can XYZ into Lyrilusc then attack for 5k then go into a 6 material Zeus, you can go into Pheonix Knightmare and Apollousa from some wipe, maybe a Verte Anaconda -> Destroyer Phoenix

- (Any Kuri-buddy) -> Linkuriboh +  Parallel eXeed 

Can get you into Verte or Pheonix, then you can link with the last eXceed into Berserker of the Tenyi. You COULD use Knightmare Unicorn instead, but tbh, Berserker of the Tenji is a fat beatstick, is immune to "target effect monster" effects like Sky Striker, and can be used with Dracoback if you can't draw your Adventure Engine, which gives you one less brick combination in your hand

- Aleister stuff -> Artemis -> Invoked Mechaba

Any amount of 1 card comboing into Mechaba :3c it's just free

- Adventure Engine

It's just the Adventure Engine. it doesn't mesh extremely well with the deck, but the incredibly easy to pull out negate can add a lot of consistency to your deck, and or stall out the enemy until you get the rest of your deck online. also, you can use Illegal Knight to summon itself and maybe help bring out Verte as well

Branded Bystial Despia deck for post PHHY format

 

I´ll try to explain the main, extra and side decks as clearly as possible. Feel free to discuss or express your opinion on the comments below

 

MAIN DECK

Despia package 

3x Aluber the Jester of Despia

Due to the new and upcoming (CYAC) support, the current deck build plays differently than the original. The endboard is no longer set Branded in Red with Ad Libitium in hand or GY, therefore, addding more despia names than necesary can led to subpar hands. Altough the Chimera play (pop 1-2 on field, draw 1-2) is strong, commiting to it forces the deck into a linear, well known, predictable play that lacks potential compared with newer combo lines. Therefore, we only play Aluber, as it´s the main deck sercher and play enabler. An argument can be made to ad 1 Despia Tragedy with Ad Libitum, but I think that the deck has better combo lines as of right now.

 

Fallen of Albaz package

2x Cartesia

Engine requierement. Two are played to avoid an accidental banish by Kashtira (Diablosis the Mind Hacker). Can be cut to 1 but it can be banished more easily, disabling Granguignol and forcing the deck into subpar combo lines

 

2x Fallen of Albaz

Engine requirement. Two is the minimun number needed to play. Can be bumped to 3 for its super poly effect when going second, but fusion deployment provides more versatility in that regard. 

 

2x Mercourier

Material requirement for Rindbrumm, and in archetype handtrap (monster effect negate) when you control a fusion monster that mentions "Fallen of Albaz" as material. Hard drawing it, alongside a Bystial, ensures your main combo is protected against Nibiru (you need to summon Rindbrumm from Branded Fusion first). 

 

1x Shrouded Dragon)

Searchable Draw power. Always send Branded Retribution to ensure recursion of your spell/traps

 

Bystial package

We run a reduced number of Bystial monster due to the expected reduced number of Tearlaments decks. Altough the number can be further reduced, its not recommended as the Bystial are engine requirements in this version of the deck (specially Saronir).

3x Bystial Lubellion

Bystial searcher and combo enabler. Can be reduced to two, but the stronger hands come from hard drawing this monster alongside Aluber/Branded Fusion.

 

3x Bystial Magnamhut

End phase searcher for any dragon on the deck. Can add Bystial Baldrake or Saronir for additional interruption on your opponent turn.

 

3x Bystial Saronir

The best Bystial for this deck, the spell/trap pitch effect is extremely handy for this deck, as it allows to search any spell when used in conjunction with a Branded retribution on grave. Can be cut to 2, as Bystial Lubellion act as additional copies. 

 

1x Bystial Baldrake

Searchable interruption. We dont run Driuswurm as I belive is the least synergetic bystial, as we don´t have a reliable way to send it to the graveyard unless you are using it as fusion material. Baldrake can banish any extra Deck monster, an interruption I believe is stronger that Driuswurm pop.

 

Branded Spell/Traps

3x Branded Opening/ 3x Branded Fusion 

Standard ratios. Opening to search Branded Fusion (or Lost). Branded Fusion so that your opponent cries about how broken is fusion summoning from the deck (it isn´t) when your resolve it. 

 

1x Branded in Red/White, 1x Branded Lost, 1x Branded Beast, 1x Branded Retibution

Only one Branded in Red as it is searchable. Branded in White is part of the new combo line. Lost allows for your fusion summons to be uninterrupted, while Branded Beast is a serchable disruption. The traps are hard bricks when drawn, so it´s my recommendation to go over 40 to reduce the chances of that happening (but not by much. 45 is the maximun I would recommend for this deck). 

 

Potential aditional spells/Traps that don´t make the cut in my proposed list

Branded Regained:  I believe it´s a "win more" card. It doesn´t give consistency to the deck when going first, it´s a brick most of the times going second due to the reduced number of Bystials, and Lost and Beast are better targets to set directly from the deck by Lubellion effect.

Branded Banishment:  Can be added as either a replacement of Red or 1x Bystial Saronir. If you don´t care of going over 43, it can be added without modifying the ratios (just expect it to see it occasionally on your opening hands). I believe that right now you either run Branded in Red or Branded Banishment, not both (specially if you don´t run Chimera)

 

Utility Cards

3x Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring and 3x Infinite Impermanence

Handtraps of choice and Crossout Designator targets, as I believe are the most impactful handtraps for PHHY format.

 

3x Crossout Designator

Allows the deck to get the edge in the mirror match and avoid the Ash on Branded Fusion (This version lacks the Patchwork engine, therefore Ash Blossom acts as a hard counter). Protects Cartesia and Aluber from Infinite Impermanence. De to  Triple Tactics Thrust, I believe Effect Veiler will see reduced usage in this format (I could be wrong).

 

 3x Fusion Deployment

Special summons either Cartesia or Albaz, helping when going second for Albaz Super Poly effect and summoning Cartesia whithout needing Albaz on grave. 

 

EXTRA DECK

Standard Branded Despia Extra Deck. New cards are Rindbrumm and Granguignol the Dusk Dragon. Rindbrumm is an extra deck monster negate that bounces a card from either field, while Ganguignol summons a Despia extra deck monster or a dogmatika main deck monster when you oponent special summons a monster by an activated monster effect (i.e., a special summon by it´s own effect). I choose to not play super poly, therefore extra deck space is not as thight. 

 

Tech Choices

Despian Proskenion: Granguignol special summon effect target. Summon it when you need a big beatstick or your opponent has a useful extra deck monster on the grave. Against non-fusion decks, Despia Quaeritis is usually a better target

Garura, Wings of Resonant Life: Granguignol send target for when you don´t need to send Albion the Branded Dragon

Predaplant Dragostapelia: For recycling a fusion with Lubellion the Searing Dragon

Baronne de Fleur: Personal tech choice for simplified game states (easily made by Cartesia+ 1 Bystial). Can definitively be cut for something else.

 

SIDE DECK

Personal choice depending on the meta where you play. Kashtira and Floowandereeze are the deck hardest matchups, so make sure your side deck helps against them

Recommended cards: 

Kashtira: Kurikara Divincarnate, Nibiru, the Primal Being, Book of Eclipse, Sphere Mode/Lava Golem (no normal summon after use)

Floowandereeze: Super Polymerization (Garua is the main target), Zombie World, Spell/Trap destruction

Spright: Dark Ruler no More, Kurikara Divincarnate

Tearlaments: Bystials, Ghost Belle & Haunted Mansion, Evenly Matched

Mirror Match: Super Polymerization, Ghost Belle & Haunted Mansion (stops Branded in Red/Banishment when Lost is not on the field). Crossout Designator, Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring. 

Triple Tactis Talent is a good card for either side or main deck.

 

SAMPLE MOST SIMPLE COMBO

Opening Hand: Branded Fusion, 1 Bystial (Except Bystial Lubellion)

 

1.Activate Branded Fusion, send Mercourier and Fallen of Albaz, summon Rindbrumm

2.Activate Bystial Saronir, Banish Mercourier, Summon Bystial. Mercourier search Cartesia

3.Special Summon Cartesia, fuse with Bystial or a monster in hand to summon Granguignol

Now, the combo branches depending on the cards on hand and the material used for the summon of Granguignol

4.1.If Cartesia fused with a Bystial (Saronir):

Cl1 Granguignol send Albion the Shrouded, Cl2 send Branded retribution, then, when the chain resolves, activate Albion effect on Gy and send branded in white. Then, add White to you hand with retribution effect. 

5.1.Use Branded in white. Fuse with Albaz in grave and Granguignol on field, banishing Albaz and sending Granguignol to Gy. Summon Mirrorjade

6.1. Cl1 Activate Mirrorjade effect, send Brigrand as cost, Cl1 negate with Rindbrumm. Chain resolves, Mirrorjade is negated, allowing us to use the effect on the next turn, and Brigrand will search Mercourier on the end phase.

7.1. End Phase. Cartesia to hand, Mercourier to hand. Endboard ends on a non target Banish (Mirrorjade), 1x monster negate (Mercourier), 1x Extra deck monster negate (Rindbrumm), summon disruption (Granguignol summons Proskenion or Quaeritis to the field).  

4.2.If Cartesia fused with a dark/light monster

 Granguignol Trigger efect sends Albion the Branded Dragon

5.2. End Phase. Cartesia to Hand, set Branded In Red (Target will be Albaz). Endboard ends on 1x extra deck monster negate (Rindbrumm), 1x summon disruption (Proskenion or Quaeritis from Granguignol), 1x Fusion disruption (Branded in Red into Lubellion-Mirrorjade, Masquerade, depending of monsters on hand)

 

The previous sample combo is the minimun power board you can make with only branded fusion and a bystial name. Aditional cards on hand (Aluber, Mercourier, Bystial Lubellion, Lost) allows for the combo to be extendend and end on aditional disruptions. I recommend to to try the deck irl or on a simulator in order to get familiarized with the main lines of play.

deck_description: This is mostly 3x the Traptrix structure deck, with a few good cards added in to make it more focused/competitive.

Did you know that (mostly) frightfur doesn't lock you out of other extra deck types? I've literally never seen anyone synchro or xyz summon with it though, which is a shame. Anyway here's what I got.

In terms of main deck, you've got basically pure frightfur, with the exception of dinowresteler coelasilat. coelasilat specials itself pretty much any time you need it to and its a level 2 tuner. Otherwise though, its frightfur gas.

Your best boards are obviously going to be mary and then something else, with the ideal best of the best board being chenying and mary.

you also have a generic 6, 7, and an 8 (I swear they come up more often then you think) and a rank 4 (doesn't come up as much, but still happens occasionaly)

Simple to play in theory, but incredibly skill based in practice. It's also incredibly funny to watch people target mary, banish a frightfur to negate it, which procs swordsoul for two more banishes. Only works once but its comedy gold.

Happy dueling

-Ornge

Hi people!

I finally got a Spright deck and following the recent results of Fur Hire/Spright-Fur Hire, I decided to build my own list. Fur Hire is a strategy I like and it fits pretty well with Spright.

Gameplan/What are you aiming for

Your goal is simple : spam your opponent of invocations to build an unbreakable board.

Basically, one exemple of board you want to finish with, could be composed of :

  • Folgo : a good body that allows you to draw when opponent's card are destroyed
  • Gigantic Spright : another good body
  • Rafale : a monster negate if you have Fur Hire cards in your hand
  • Spright Carrot and/or Spright Red for more negates

One point you must take care of, is to manage correctly your ressources to not burn all your options too quickly. Otherwise, the deck is sensitive on your normal summon : you have to play around this threat.

Thoughts around deckbuilding

I tried to have a strict 40-card decklist. Moreover, as the deck is really sensitive to Nibiru (and Infinite Impermanence), I would include a tech card to prevent this handtraps : Crossout Designator !

For the other ratio : 

  • Beat, Bladesman Fur Hire is not that mandatory as we run Spright with the deck. Two is fine. The most important Fur Hire monster to have is Rex and he allows us the access to Beat quiet easilly. This reflection is still the same for Spright Starter. 
  • Obviously, the ban of Spright Elf is annoying for us. But we still have Gigantic Spright and Spright Sprind , which are good for our strategy. I think the Extra Deck is overall classic. However, the only spicy thing is to have Donner, Dagger Fur Hire at two. As we run Pot of Prosperity and we play with Spright, I believe this ratio to be enough.

 

As usual, this decklist is probably improvable (especially the Side deck). So if you have advises/feedbacks, it will be welcomed :)
Enjoy guys!

deck_excerpt: A rather fun and Original Control Deck
deck_description:
This Deck plays mainly around three cards : Angelic Statue - Azurune, The embodiment of Apophis and Statue of Anguish Pattern. These three cards are your main way to interact with your opponent, as Azurune negates a summon, Apophis negates up to three or four monster effects and Anguish Pattern can pop cards on a non-once per turn. To help them, three monsters can be really useful : Qardan the great Sage help you recover your ressources and gives you the ability to play something a trap on your first turn, Pharaonic Advent gets you any trap you need and Lord of the Heavenly Prison can protect your traps and can get you anyone of them if you activate another. 

After that, every pot is here for consistency and the other are tech cards that can be useful in some situations. For the extra Deck, its mostly a toolbox that you make to attack and put pressure, I play the rank-ups only for fun, dont be afraid of replacing them if you feel like it. 

This Deck is more of a fun Deck (more for you than for your opponent probably) because of the general lack of good trap monsters except of your main three, but with the right hand you can probably beat lots of Decks. I hope you'll have fun playing or just learning that this Deck existed.

deck_name: Ghostrick but not like you expect
deck_excerpt: Ghostrick like you never saw it.
deck_description:
Ghostrick is famous for being the worst at doing their own XyZ monsters. So, what about we dont do them ? Thats the whole point of this Deck. This Deck plays like Guru control except its fun ! Your main objective and way to interrupt is to flip your opponents monster with stuff like Sol and Luna or Destructive Daruma Karma Canon which help you flipping your slow Ghostrick monsters. Siren act as a wonderful searcher : if you need an interruption, take Ghostrick or treat, if you want a reborn, take Shot, you need one of your fields, take em ! Nekomosume is also a great card in this Deck, making almost every Deck twice as slow and giving you tempo. 

But you might wonder, how do we win ? Thats where the last cards come in play. The best card in this Deck without a doubt is Ghostrick Night. This Trap card has the simple effect to prevent your oponent to flip monsters. This might seem useless, but this whole Deck is made to flip your opponents monsters, which will eventually end up in youre opponent having no space to summon anything. And then, thats where your field spells come in play. These card allow both players to attack directly if every monster their opponent controls is face-down, allowing you to slowly - but surely ! - to kill your opponent. 

Since you dont use your Extra Deck very much, Pot of Prosperity allow you to take the piece you need to complete your hand. Finally, Terrors in the Hidden City is a nice tech card that protects your backrow and your set Ghostricks and can allow your Ghostricks to walk over big boss monsters easily.

At the end of the day, Its still a Ghostrick Deck and you cannot make magically this Deck great. But this one can work quite well against quite powerful Deck, just dont be afraid of bricking...

I hope you liked the Deck, and have a nice day / week / month / year / life !

deck_excerpt: ABC | Ancient Fairy Dragon | Therion | Adventure | Bestial
deck_description:
Post Photon Hypernova & Febraury Banlist ABC deck.

I'll give it more thought later, curious how I would run Triple Tactics Thrust.

COMBO | Union Hangar & Destrudo

Requirements

-Union Hangar

-Destrudo in hand or GY

 

End Board
- ABC-Dragon Buster

-King Regulus

-Ancient Fairy Dragon

-I:P

-Platinum Gadget

-Therion Discolosseum

Steps

  1. Activate Union Hangar to add B.

  2. Summon B & activate Union Hangar to equip Union Driver to B.

  3. Activate Union Driver to banish it for C.

  4. Activate C to unequip and special summon it.

  5. Link summon Platinum Gadget (using B and C) & activate B to search A from deck.

  6. Activate Platinum Gadget to special summon A.

  7. Activate Destrudo to special summon itself.

  8. Synchro summon Ancient Fairy Dragon & activate A to add B from GY to hand.

  9. Activate Ancient Fairy Dragon to destroy Union Hangar (gain 1000 LP) and search Therion Discolosseum from deck.

  10. Activate Therion Discolosseum to search King Regulus from deck.

  11. Special summon King Regulus targetting A.

  12. Activate A to unequip and special summon it.

  13. Link summon I:P Masquerena (using A and B) & activate B to search B from deck.

  14. Fusion summon ABC.

deck_excerpt: "Life will find a way to blow up Babycerasaurus."
deck_description:
Debuting in Wild Survivors, Transcendrake are unearthed! They aim to destroy cards and utilize the aid of normal monsters to make various ED monsters.

So does these cards help dinos to go back to their pre-historic reign of 2020? Lets find out!

Chapter 1:

Part 1: Evolution (Drakes)

  • Ground Xeno - Let's start with the best card! Basically 3 extras copies of Fossil Dig and Scrap Raptor , but you can also add Xeno Meteoros which this card's effect after adding the card triggers by destroying a card in hand, if you destroy Babycerasaurus or Petiteranodon you can summon Souleating Oviraptor , Scraptor or Xeno. This card also has a GY effect to fuse using monsters from your hand/field to make Transcendrake Gigantozowler .
  • Xeno Meteoros - The only main deck Transcendrake monster I run, his evo is too much of a brick and a worse Ultimate Conductor Tyranno . Xeno can summon itself when any card on either field is destroyed! And considering what dinos like to do... This card is also a level 6 tuner which means you can make Baronne de Fleur or use its effect that locks you to summon a normal dino monster from deck like Frostosaurus to make Evolzar Solda which is 2 pops on cards that are summoned or their xyz monster Transcendrake Drillgnathus .

Overall the maindeck cards are the ones that stand out really... the ED monsters are somewhat lacking, you'd be better off doing your plays and going into Baronne with Xeno, but for a first view of this Series is okaish. (Note we still have 1 spell/trap card missing for them)

Part 2: Fossils (Dinos)

  • Souleating Oviraptor - Searches any Dino like Dogoran, the Mad Flame Kaiju to get rid of towers or tower-lites, the babies to pop with Ground Xeno or Scraptor, you can also pop a dino to revive from GY which has interactions with Lost World to destroy 2 dinos in the deck.
  • Miscellaneousaurus - One of the most insane type support ever printed. Protection from effects and a way to summon cards from your deck like Animadorned Archosaur by banishing itself to fetch Double Evolution Pill to bring forth Ultimate Conductor Tyranno . Misc also helps to set-up for Drillgnathus.
  • Babycerasaurus and Petiteranodon - Non opt summon from deck, if you see these gremlins in the field or hand make sure to blow them up as much as you can.
  • Animadorned Archosaur - You will also be using this fella to commit infanticide, you can summon him via banishing Misc from grave, it also gets you the Pills and you can link him into Linkuriboh and then Secure Gardna to use your pills.
  • Giant Rex - Big bungus that comes back when banished, so you can banish him with your UCT, Pill or Misc.
  • Dinowrestler Pankratops and Dogoran, the Mad Flame Kaiju - Removal that dodges target and free out to any problem! (singular)
  • Ultimate Conductor Tyranno - Destroys a dino to Book of Eclipse , can attack all monsters your opponent controls doing 1k burn for each, triggers your babies, transcendrakes and scraptor, you can demolish decks like kash by just tributing 1 monster to stop their antics.
  • Doodle Beast - Stego , Doodle Beast - Tyranno and Doodlebook - Uh uh uh! - Free body, disruption during your opponent's turn and search of big dinos like Dogoran.

Part 3: Scrapyard (Scraptor engine)

  • Scrap Raptor , Scrap Chimera and Scrap Wyvern - Scraptor when destroyed by another Scrap's effect lets him normal summon another scrap and search Chimera which can summon him from the GY, you can use the Scraptor to make Wyvern which can revive the Scraptor, destroy it, summon another Scraptor and blow up the wyvern so you can go into Borreload Savage Dragon and have mats to go into another R4nk.

Part 4: Extras 

  • Evolzar Dolkka - Monster Negate.
  • Evolzar Laggia - Solemn on legs.

Chapter 2:

Part 1: Spells

  • Fossil Dig - Better Reinforcement of the Army .
  • Double Evolution Pill - Summons Ultimate Conductor Tyranno and Dinowrestler Pankratops , but mostly the first one.
  • Dragonic Diagram and True King Lithosagym, the Disaster - Destroys a card on field or hand to add Lithos which can destroy up to 2 monsters on the field or hand to rip 3 card's from your opponent's extra deck.
  • Lost World - Allows raptor to destroy cards from your own deck while having an stats lowering effect.

Final Thoughts: The deck is basically just an excuse to give dinos a easier way into Baronne and 3 fossil digs, Ground Xeno is an incredible card that can be used in a lot of decks that like blowing up stuff like Unchained or Nepts if you decide to run a scraptor engine, but thats really it the deck is just a little toolbox for dinos that require you to run a normal monster in a deck of high level monsters.

deck_excerpt: List showcased for the Traptrix Discord.
deck_description:
This is also the list seen in the r/yugioh Traptrix Discord with over 1K users with the goal being to provide a sample list for those who are interested in deckbuilding. If you didn't come here from the Traptrix server, there is also more info on what the generally agreed Traptrix deck skeleton looks like in #pit-dwellers-starting-guide along with other details but it isn't a necessity or anything.

https://discord.gg/aGY2mvUc2a

This list for the TCG showcases the standard-ish Traptrix ratios (First 23 cards) and decent generic cards on a low-mid budget.

Notes:

The only glaring thing that pops out in the main deck is the inclusion of only 2 copies of IDP. (Ice Dragon's Prison) With it being a HOPT, you don't want to open multiples. If you ever want a third copy, just play Called By The Grave instead.Yes, you do want Vesiculo as a one of in Pure. Completely earns the spot. The "Tech Hole" Terrifyng Trap Hole (Formerly Delusion) could essentally be any other Hole to cover match ups where Floodgate is meh. (Bottomless, Nightmare, Treacherous, Void, Break-off another copy of Floodgate, ect.)

It's not yet entirely proven but it could seem promising. So Evenly is in the Side Deck atm. The side deck (the one ofs especially) is comprised of many useful and previously played cards that have been shown to work well in Traptrix before. Durendal with Droll is so sacky if Droll ever becomes relevant.

Budget alternatives

Swap out Pot of Prosperity for 3x Parallel Exceed. Not a replace functionally but you tend to want to grab an extender for the most part. (Run Link spider if you do. Very much mandatory to do so to make the other extenders function with Exceed if needed.)

Most of the generic ED cards don't have 1-1 replacements but more of alternatives that are managable.

Zeus > Exciton Knight.

Underworld Goddess > Borrelsword (For taking care of big boss monsters.)

The Ptolemaeus package doesn't have alternatives. You can fill in with space with other generics or tech options. ex: Abyss Dweller. Tornado Dragon. I:P for a generic link 2 to run and Underworld Goddess synergy. A second Pinguicula. Maybe Beetrooper Armor Horn for easier kill setups into Atypus?

Ptolemaeus Package explained

Traptrix hates Evenly so having two ways to avoid it seems great but the other application is for going against Triple Tactics Thrust. It's standard to make Ptolemaeus with 3 materials so that Durendal has 2 Xyz Materials for 2 disruptions. It's also pretty adaptable. You can make Ptolemaeus with 2 materials to have Durendal with 1 mat if you don't want/can't invest 3 mats. Pairs well with Droll as mentioned before.

What do I banish off of Prosperity?

Think of keeping the essentials. Keep the first 5 ED monsters I have in the list. (Maybe switch Redoer for Rafflesia or vice versa to banish.) Then keep whatever you think would come up during the match. (ex: If you aren't making Diamond to stick on field, banish 1 copy of Ptolemaeus. Banish Cularia or Bagooska if you aen't expecting a grind game. ect.)

Dark World es una strategia bastante particular, Dark World aparacio por primera vez en el juego en el sobre de expansión ELEMENTAL ENERGY en 2005. Al ellos ser descartados activarán efecto. Es un arquetipo de oscuridad y tipo fiend. Dark world tuvo un reestructurado hace poco en diciembre del año pasado reviviendo su primera carta de fusión que tiene sinergia sí el oponente activa algún efecto. No es una estrategia que puede llegar modo competitivo, pero sin duda de la mano de los monstruos ¡DANGER! le dieron un aire nuevo a la estrategia. TRASLATE: Dark World is a very particular strategy, Dark World appeared for the first time in the game in the ELEMENTAL ENERGY expansion pack in 2005. When they are discarded they will activate an effect. It is an archetype of darkness and a fiend type. Dark world had a recent revamp in December of last year reviving its first fusion card that has synergy if the opponent activates an effect. It is not a strategy that can reach competitive mode, but without a doubt at the hands of the monsters DANGER! they gave a new air to the strategy.

deck_excerpt: Even if they are gone, their corpses will be used once again.
deck_description:
A deck for Domain Format. https://discord.gg/jGkRCJkt3d Join the Discord if you wanna see more!

I love my normal summons. 
Especially when I can normal summon Lonefire Blossom as many times as I can gain NS every turn!
Grab any plant with just a normal summon!

Use Cucumber Horse and Rikka Petal to loop, grabbing any monster you want out of the GY during every battle phase!
Revive Mardel, Generaider Boss of Light  -> grab more Plants from Deck
Revive Cattycorn -> Grab more Field Spells
Revive Fairy Archer -> More Monsters!

Party to your hearts dreams! Being sent to the GY is not the end of it!

Turn 1 Combo: 3 interruptions + Cucumber Horse in GY
https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=1038951-46823970
Sunavalon Bloom Predaplant Dragostapelia Teardrop the Rikka Queen 

Intro

Let’s abuse the power of soft-OPT Lonefire Blossom  with  Normal Summoning  it over and over from the DMZ!
I’ve added the new Circle of the Fairies , the monster Aromage Jasmine , as well as copious amounts of Double Summon, because each copy becomes just an Emergency Teleport for plants by normal summoning a Lonefire from DMZ!
In addition, I feature Cucumber Horse Looping Mardel, Generaider Boss of Light in my deck, abusing the large # of battle phases that will occur! (To add a plant every time Mardel is summoned)
Rikka Petal will summon itself out every End Phase! The free body allows for easy resource advantage turn after turn.

Plants have several strengths that translate well into Domain:

1. Swarming the Field/searching the deck
2. Summoning From GY
3. LP gain

All of these are present within engine and easily recurable, tied together by the powerful normal summon-able Lonefire Blossom 

Main Combo

My starting board will consist of only 3 interruptions, but also sets up a loop of Rikka Petal , Mardel, Generaider Boss of Light , and Cucumber Horse  working together to add 1 plant monster to hand in every battle phase that occurs.
This will allow you to mount a powerful comeback on your turn: summoning out many of the searched plants, accessing destruction effects, and generally maintaining a resisliant board
https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=1038951-46823970   

Turn 2 Combo

You would like to use Lonefire to grab Fairy Archer Ingunar out of the deck, in order to revive either your Predaplant Dragostapelia  (if dead) or Circle of the Fairies  (to extend)
Once thats done, (by its own effect) summon out the Rose Girl / Spore you searched, and go into a synchro play! Use Rikka Petal to add Primula the Rikka Fairy to fix levels. Making Aromaseraphy Sweet Marjoram  will allow you to have Blessed Winds , which recycles your plants and revives Aromaseraphy Jasmine . Or you can go into your other options!

 

Other Pieces

There are also some other elements to raise the ceiling of this deck:

() Naturia Camellia : 

- Sends Naturia Sunflower  to GY and Special Summons it on opponents turn
- Use with Naturia Sunflower to negate 1-2 monsters per turn
- Summon this directly with Lonefire Blossom (if an additional normal summon can be spent on summoning Lonefire)

() Cattycorn 

- Can add any field spell in the game, as long as your field spell zone is empty
- Loop this with Cucumber Horse 

() Aromaseraphy Sweet Marjoram 

- Adds Blessed Winds :
Special summon Aromaseraphy Jasmine  from GY 
Gain LP and shuffle back a plant to deck (triggers Jasmine's effect to add plant to hand)
- Destroys a card when you gain LP

() Fairy Knight Ingunar 

XYZ Rank 6 made with 3 materials
- opponent cannot react to its effect 
- return all cards on the field to the hand
- easily made with Fairy Archer Ingunar  summoning Snowdrop the Rikka Fairy  from GY. Snowdrop copys Fairy Archer's level (6). XYZ with petal + Snowdrop + Fairy Archer

 

Misc Info

Here is a priority list for Mardel, Generaider Boss of Light adds:

1. Rikka Princess 
2. Cattycorn
3. Therion "Lily" Borea 
4. (Tuner Monsters)
5. Fairy Archer Ingunar 
6. Predaplant Spider Orchid (To set Pendulum Scales)

Cucumber Horse Revial Priority List:

1. Mardel, Generaider Boss of Light 
2. Cattycorn
3. Mudan the Rikka Fairy 
4. Fairy Archer Ingunar 
5. Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio 
7. Staysailor Romarin 
8. Sunvine Healer 

Enjoy planting!

deck_excerpt: The Bystials find a new home with those nice people from the church.
deck_description:
With the recent banlist trying to end the life of those sea people from tearlament, some people thought that the bystials would drop off too. Well I'm here to say no to that with this deck list that can stand up to the meta. This is Bystial Dogmatika.

The main focus of this deck is to outgrind your opponent, keeping their resources low while you build advantage ad infinitum. The way the deck accomplishes this is by utilizing the synergies the light Dogmatika monsters have and their ability to dump extra deck Light and Dark monsters for the bystials to utilize to summon themselves. The ritual monsters all focus on ripping cards out of the opponents extra deck, keeping them off their sure to be powerful monsters. This deck was playable before photon hypernova but 2 new cards in that set make this playstyle a lot more consitant and targeted. I will go over those cards soon, but for now lets look at the cards one by one. 

Nibiru: This is just my personal format handtrap call alone with called by the grave and Triple tact. Nibiru does a number on a Kashtira board, while called by and triple tact is for the miriad of handtraps creeping back into the format. 

The chaos monsters: One thing this deck does very well is fill up the grave with light and dark monsters, either from the main deck or extra deck. Both chaos monsters are searchable off chaos space. Levi is an all purpose destruciton tool, while Creator is used to refill your resouces, either to the main or extra deck. Though remember you do have to be able to summon 1 of the 3 monsters you target with his effect. Both are level 8 so with Lubellion they make an easy dingirsu or other level 8 you choose to play. And when you open with them, you can just pitch them with chaos space to search lubellion and combo off from there.

The Bystial Package: All the dragons(worth playing) are here. While Tear might not be around every corner anymore, these guys are still potentially walking d.d. crows and can keep you going on resources, interaction, and GY setup. Branded beast + Branded Regained is still a pretty nice setup.

Ecclesia and Fleurdelis: Standard memebers of the Dogmatika package. In my experience, these are the guys you will end up summoning off of Chaos Creator.

Dogmatika Alba Zoa: Ok so maybe the church was hiding a gigantic monster inside. Alba Zoa comes out with a beefy 4k ATK/DEF and makes all your dogmatika monster unaffected by the activated affects of extra deck monsters. His effect isnt as good as i wish as when you activate it, your opponent gets to choose which effect they apply to themselves. Either they send cards from their hand/ED, 1 card for every 2 cards in their ED, or they return all extra deck monsters on their field to the ED. Obviously if the opponent has no ED monsters on their field they have to pick the first effect but it can still be annoying. Mainly cause if you dont know what they are on, the opponent might just send a bunch of stuff from the extra they want in the grave, like Ntss, or tri-brigade monsters. But it still is the biggest body in the deck so worth playing. 

White Knight of Dogmatika: This is the monster you want to try and end on going first. Upon resolution of an opponents card or effect, you get to send a monster of your choice from both EDs. You can send anything form ntss to destroy something, herald to search, ignister or fossil for next turn, etc while taking a monster from your oppoents. 

White Relic of Dogmatika: While pretty weak compared to the other 2 rituals, she round out the monsters by being a decent playmaker herself. She triggers the ED dump when the opponent summons somthing from the ED but I have gotten more use out of her on summon effect since she doesnt reduce the monster she targets, you can target your own Alba Zoa and make her a massive 4500atk. 

Dogmatikamatrix: This is other new Dogmatika card in PHHY, and it feels busted. It searches any Dogmatika ritual spell or ritual monster, then if your opponent controls something, you search any Dogmatika card. Just go plus 2 cause who cares. And while you control a ritual monster, you can look in either players ED and dump something. Now while you can only activate 1 Dogmatikamatrix per turn, the ED dump is not a hard once per turn. Which means if you control muliples of this card, you get to dump multiple times. Just unbelievable.

Dogmatikalamity: This is the better of the 2 dogmatika ritual cards. Your sends for each monster are as follows: Alba Zoa = Five-headed dragon. White Knight = Psy-Frame Omega or Titinklad(depends on board), White Relic = Herald or Ntss (again, depends on the boardstate.) 

Chaos Space: This is a part of your setup as well as grind game. Depending on what you pitch, you can search either chaos monster, lubellion, or 2 of the ritual monsters. It can also recycle those monsters as well as any ED monsters that have been banished to net you another draw. 

Extra Deck: while you dont go into the extra often since the dogmatika cards lock you, that doesnt mean you can still utilize it. the links can be cut for other ED dumps, as well as Digirsu. Omega actually turn into the star of the show late game, since dumping him means you can recycle your ritual spells, ntss, chaos monsters, ect. 

 

PROS AND CONS:

Pros:

1. You have a lot of individually powerful cards. Nadir, lubelion, dogmatikamatrix, chaos space, all have the potential to plus you to the moon. 

2. Extra deck hate is good again. Kashtier and branded don't look so strong when their big boss monsters are stuck in the GY

3. You have a great grind game. With all the recycling, drawing, and searching this deck can do, you are more favored the longer the game lasts. 

Cons.

1. You are still playing a ritual deck, which means you can end up stairing at a hand of some bystials, handtraps, and ritual monster but no spell. Bricks gonna Brick

2. Shockingly from my playtesting, Labyrinth is your biggest issue. They can outgrind you for days and don't care one bit for the extra deck or Ritual monsters. I would suggest focusing some side deck slots for that matchup

3. Macro effects are going to be an issue. You are ok with stuff getting banished, its just you want to be the one banishing them. 

 

If you have suggestions or questions about this deckbuild, please let me know below, i would love to hear some feedback.

deck_excerpt: “Everybody is going to be dead one day, just give them time.”
deck_description:
This deck uses my one of my favourite cards of all time, and turns it into an absolutely devestating force! This card of course, is "Bad Reaction to Simochi", a card that whenever an opponent would gain life points, they would lose that much instead.

This deck is mostly made for Master Duel and was made by Duel Logs. Go and check out his video/channel for more awesome Yu-Gi-Oh! content!

This deck is meant to be a Masterduel/ocg deck as Fairytail-Snow and Chicken Game are unbanned. You want to try to end your turn with 3 Fairytail- Snow in the graveyard along with your 3 Necroface. You also want to end the turn with 18 or more cards in the graveyard total along with 2 Burial from a different dimension set to your field. If you can achieve this you can win the duel.

Use foolish burial to try to dump Fairtail - Snow to the graveyard. The danger engine also gives the 3 different types to go into Curious, the Lightsworn Domain as another way to dump Snow. Make sure whenever you draw a Burial form a Different dimension to set it to your field so it doesn't get hit by a Danger! If you do get a choice of a monster to banish with Allure of Darkness do not banish Necorface as you might banish useful combo pieces such as Snow.

The Uni-Zombies is the main card you want to normal summon as it can dump Necroface to the Graveyard for later. It also has an added bonus with the fact that you can discard Danger! cards to activate their effects.

 

Before your oppoenents draw phase since Fairytail snow is a Quick Effect you want to banish 7 cards from your graveyard to special summon her. You must banish the 3 Necroface here. Then actiave Burial from a different dimension to return the 3 Necroface to the graveyard. Now you activate the next Fairytail-Snow to banish the 3 Necroface again to summon her to the field. Now you activate your 2nd Burial from a different dimension to return the Necroface to the graveyard. You activate the the 3rd and final Snow banishing the 3 Necroface so you have banished your oppoenent entire deck.

Use the Drytrons and Benten to facilitate the Ritual Summon of Herald of Ultimateness and also have Eva in hand to keep negating while reloading for fairies. Lastly push for game with Draconids/Quadrantids!
a Dragon Link Deck Featuring Bystials

deck_excerpt: "Lævatein is there, that Lopt with runes Once made by the doors of death; In Loki's chest by Sinmora lies it, And nine locks fasten it firm"
deck_description:
Generaiders hail from the deckbuilding pack Mystic Fighters which introduced Dragon Maids and Mathmechs both which had showings in the meta, but now with the support in Photon Hypernova in the form of Vala, Seidhr of the Generaider Bosses and Laevatein, Generaider Boss of Shadows generaiders have finally a way to compete! So let's take a look at what they have instored for us!

Chapter 1:

Part 1: The 9 realms and its bosses (Generaiders)

Generaiders is a control'ish strategy that revolves around the field spell Generaider Boss Stage to summon out your monsters, most being level 9. Now that may sound scary to some people and you may ask yourself: "Isn't that brick.dek?" while that was the case in the past the newer support helps them benefit from having those monsters in hand, so lets get into the meat of it.

  • Generaider Boss Stage - The field allows you to summon 1 Generaider monster from your deck if your opponent adds a card from their main Deck to their hand, meaning this triggers during the Draw Phase and if you summoned a monster during your opponent's turn you get to summon as many Generaider tokens as possible but they are destroyed during the endphase. Now lets start with the tokens actually, thats the fuel for your Generaider bosses, they can tribute Generaider/Monsters of the same type to apply their effects if any and the tokens are a way to minigate wasting too much resources. As for the first effect their boss Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity or Generaider Boss Room can trigger the effect so you can summon a boss during your turn for extra bodies for XYZs, which the R9nk pool has some insane targets for which I will get to later... If you really need it Metaverse and Generaider Boss Fight can both active the field, with Fight also giving you a boss and being searcheable by Generaider Boss Quest .
  • Harr, Generaider Boss of Storms - Let's start with arguably one of the best bosses, Harr is your Omni-Negate and the boss you will be summoning most of the time with boss stage for your first turn, Harr also has great synergy with your other cards that cause the opponent to draw since it makes your opponent send a monster from Hand or Field to the GY akin to Apoqliphort Towers .
  • Mardel, Generaider Boss of Light - You may recognize this lady from the Aromaseraphy Jasmine combos that plant decks go into, Mardel adds any Generaider card you may need, you will normally summon her in your turn with Loptr, Shadow of the Generaider Bosses , Vala, Seidhr of the Generaider Bosses or World Legacy Monstrosity targetting one of your Level 9s.
  • Utgarda, Generaider Boss of Delusion - Quick-effect banish for 2 tributes, incredible removal and great disruption.
  • Hela, Generaider Boss of Doom - Like Mardel, this boss is the only other one used in Pile Decks being able to tribute a Generaider/Zombie monster to revive a Gene or Zomb from your GY, helping a lot in the grindy games by reviving bosses like Utgarda/Harr to keep disrupting your opponent or Loptr/Vala to Generaite more resources.
  • Nidhogg, Generaider Boss of Ice - Negates Special Summons that don't start a chain, you cannot negate the summon of something that was summoned with Polymerization but you can negate summons from the ED like Contact Fusions, Synchros, XYZs, Links. If it's effects were like Solemn Judgment this guy would be a 2-3 of.
  • Vala, Seidhr of the Generaider Bosses - The new boss for the Deck, Vala can send 1 Generaider card from your Hand to summon her from your Hand or GY and if she is Special Summoned she can Summon a boss from your Hand or Grave. Vala basically says "Free R9nk" and helps you remove bricks and put them on the field/GY.
  • Loptr, Shadow of the Generaider Bosses - Loki can tribute 1 Generaider monster to summon a boss from deck, and during your opponent's turn all generaider bosses gain 1000ATK/DEF, helping you push for game/pressure your opponent.
  • Laevatein, Generaider Boss of Shadows and Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity - The 2 archetypal R9nk XYZs, Laevatein like Loki has an ATK/DEF manipulation, causing your opponent's monsters to lose 1000ATK/DEF, it can also tribute itself to tag out into Jormungandr and then you can attach cards from either field or grave as material up to the number of XYZ material this card had to the special summoned monster. This card is just insane! Free removal for monsters like Mekk-Knight Crusadia Avramax , GY effects or annoying backrow/Monsters. As for Jormungandr its a big bungus that gains 1000ATK/DEF x the number of materials it has and it can detach 1 material to make both players draw and attach a card from their hand or field to it, this might seem bad at first but it triggers your Boss Stage and Harr's handrip effect meaning you can win if your opponent is relying on a tower monster with an empty hand.

Part 2: Crowley and the Ghosts (Invoked and Handtraps)

  • Aleister the Invoker , Magical Meltdown , Invocation , Artemis, the Magistus Moon Maiden , Invoked Mechaba . Invoked Augoeides and Invoked Elysium - Aleister's use here is to go into Mechaba to get negates against handtraps or cards like Evenly Matched , or just bait ash. You will be summoning him, getting Invocation and going into Artemis to make Mechaba which can omni as long as you have cards of the same type that were activated in your hand, its also a Level 9 monster which allows the use of World Legacy Monstrosity to summon 2 bosses that aren't Light Attribute from your Deck, which kinda hurts because you want to summon Mardel but eh. As for the other Invoked monsters Invoked Augoeides can pop a card and help swing for game by banishing a Invoked in grave and Invoked Elysium gets rid of every monster in your opponent's board as long as they have the same attribute.
  • Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring , Ghost Mourner & Moonlit Chill , Effect Veiler and Infinite Impermanence - These are here to stop Kash in their way, I dont think it will be the top meta deck but people will certainly be running it, Mourner and Veiler helps to deal with the matchup specifically + Mourner not being able to be Bystial'ed but also work as generics.

Part 3: Extra Deck

  • Mereologic Aggregator , El Shaddoll Winda , El Shaddoll Apkallone and Shaddoll Schism - Aggregator is a R9nk that can send a card from your ED to the GY meaning you can send Apkallone to add Schism so you can make Winda in the opponent's turn using Aggregator/Harr.
  • Nine-Lives Cat - Summons back a Level 9 from your GY or your opponent's GY.
  • Sacred Tree Beast, Hyperyton - Like Mechaba, Funny negate you can go into.

Chapter 2:

Part 1: Spells/Traps

  • Generaider Boss Quest - Fetches you Boss Stage and Room by shuffling back a boss.
  • World Legacy Monstrosity - Free summon from hand/deck.
  • Generaider Boss Room - Negates cards that activate in response to your Generaider effects for a discard and changes the effect to "Each players draws 1 card" helping you to pull off Harr's effect.

Example of a simple Combo:

Normal Summon Aleister which Add Invocation > Summon Artemis > Invocation Summons Mechaba > Invocation adds back Aleister > World Legacy Monstrosity summons Vala/Harr/Nidhogg > Make Laevateinn. You have an Omni and a steal 2 cards.

Final Thoughts:

The new Support fixes and makes the deck way better, giving it consistency and more pressure. Hopefully we will get another card of support that ties them in with Runicks which shares the same Lore.

predapianta prova

Nouvellez is a ritual deck introduced in Wild Survivor focused on tributing monsters to go into their higher level ritual monsters and summon uh... Hungry Burger? Well let's get into it!

Some notes:

  • Why no level 1 or 2 since they can be used with Pre-Prep?: Makes the Target chain longer making you go minus + the Impcantation engine can fetch you all you need.
  • Why 1 Ritual Spell?: The thing can get Ashed and Belle'ed and you do not want this to happen, at least Inception can recover itself.
  • Why Mikanko?: Disruption and equips target.
  • Why no Libromancer and Drytron?: Big engines that dont help you fetch the Ritual spell/monsters.

Chapter 1:

Part 1: Hell's Kitchen (Nouvellez)

  • Poêlétis de Nouvellez - Draws 1 when ritual summoned and when any card on the field is targeted by effect or for an attack you can tribute 1 face-up card in either field and itself to summon a Lv5 Nouvellez from Deck or Hand, since we want faster chains I chose not to run the lower level Nouvellez and go straigh from Lv3 to Lv5 which is one of their better monsters.
  • Balameuniere de Nouvellez - When summoned Adds a "Nouvellez" or "Recipe" card and it can Quick-Effect tribute a face-up monster your opponent controls to summon Baegriller de Nouvellez from your Deck or Hand. You will mostly be adding their field Nouvellez Auberge "À Table" to add the counter trap.
  • Baegriller de Nouvellez - Dark Ruler No More on summon, if it was summoned by a Nouvellez effect it tribute's every monsters your opponent controls, and as Quick-Effect it can tribute 1 face-up monster your opponent controls to summon Hungry Burger from your Deck or Hand.
  • Nouvellez Auberge "À Table" - When activated you can add a "Recipe" card, during main phase you can shuffle back a ritual from your Hand into the Deck to draw 1 card and during the endphase of your turn you can recycle 2 cards in the GY including a "Recipe" card and you draw 1 card.
  • Hungry Burger and Recette de Spécialité - Chef's Specialty Recipe - Specialty Recipe is your Infernity barrier with a GY effect to mass tribute cards if hungry burger was summoned, this card can be shuffled back with Auberge. Hungry Burger is only used here because you get 2 extra interruptions.
  • Recette de Poisson - Fish Recipe - In here this is a normal ritual spell, problem with it is that both Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring and Ghost Belle & Haunted Mansion can shoot the spell down, making it less desirable.

Part 2: Centerpieces (Impcantations)

All Impcantations effect monsters have the effect to summon themselves and another name from Deck if you reveal a ritual monster/spell in your hand.

  • Impcantation Talismandra - Adds a ritual monster from your Deck which most of the time will be Ohime the Manifested Mikanko or Poêlétis de Nouvellez .
  • Impcantation Candoll - Adds a ritual spell from your Deck which most of the time will be Impcantation Inception .
  • Impcantation Penciplume - Adds a ritual monster from your GY which can be your discarded Impcantation Chalislime .
  • Impcantation Chalislime - Discards a card to summon an Impcantation monster from your Deck.
  • Impcantation Inception - Normal ritual spell but its second effect allows you to send an impcantation from your Hand or Field to the GY to add the spell back and summon another impcantation from your Deck.
  • Honorable mention to Preparation of Rites which searches your entire ritual monster line-up.

Part 3: Dancers of the Citrine Goddess (Mikankos) 

  • Ohime the Manifested Mikanko searches all your Mikanko cards, you can search Mikanko Water Arabesque to bounce back your Impcantations to be able to summon from your ED cards like Dyna Mondo or go int othe R6nk pool which this Deck can access via Diviner of the Herald sending Herald of the Arc Light , Baegriller, Hungry Burger, Benten or Ohime.
  • Mikanko Water Arabesque - Can bounce a card in either field to summon Ha-Re the Sword Mikanko which then adds Mikanko Purification Dance to trigger your Lv3 Ritual after its equipped.

Main Combo:

Plume reveals Poeletis > SS itself and Candoll > Add Inception > Inception tribute Cand to summon Poeletis > Draw 1 > Inception summons Talismandra > Add Ohime > Ohime reveals add Arabesque and discard what you drew with the ritual if its not useful > Arabesque equip and effect on Talismandra to summon Ha-re > Ha-re Adds Purifying dance > Poeletis tributes both to summon Balameuniere that adds A Table > A Table fetches Chef's Special Recipe > Use Inception in hand to summon Ohime and Discard to equip Pure.

So you end on 2 tributes with Balameuniere and Baegriller, 1 S/T omni via the trap, 1 mass tribute via the trap's gy effect, 1 bounce with dance.
Nouvelles Burger (Feb 2023)

deck_excerpt: Bystial Ishizu Tearlaments / YCS Lyon Top 32
deck_description:
Category: Tournament Meta Deck

Tournament Meta Decks are current-level Meta Decks that are capable of going up against the best of the best. These are curated lists that cannot be uploaded by regular users.

Creator: Joo-Ho Ahn (@Korean)

Tournament: YCS Lyon - February 12th 2023

Placement: Top 32

//////////////////////////////////Basic combos:

Note: Some combos I did when Spright Elf was still in the game but now that he's banned you can disregard the moves you link summon to him.

 

https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=813757-46457912

Archosaur + Babycerasaurus or Petiteranodon

(Archosaur + Baby = Oviraptor + Babycerasaurus = Miscellaneousaurus + Baby = Oviraptor + Miscellaneousaurus)

 

https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=813757-46747937

Full Combo from the deck = the difference is that you don't play around Hand traps but end up doing an extra XYZ or SYNCHRO.

 

https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=813757-46748268

Lost World + Oviraptor

 

https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=813757-46458731

Lost World + Scrap Raptor

 

https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=813757-46748483

Scrap Raptor + Miscellaneosaurus

 

Doodle Beast is a card that has a very interesting role in the deck because it replaces the role that previously could only be played by a card outside the engine that is the Token Collector in synergy with Lost World.

https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=813757-46750196

Lost World + Babycerasaurs + Doodle Beast

or

https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=813757-46750331

Lost World + Archosaur + Doodle Beast (even if it's Archosaur a Normal Summon you can still do Full Combo)

 

- Here you can summon the Doodle Beast and destroy the Token on the opponent's field to make a Full Combo.

- Another interesting point is that it can be a way for you to play around effects that target your Dinosaur monsters so you don't lose to a hand trap in Normal Summon like Infinite Impermanence for example.

- You can add to the hand with Oviraptor which means that in hands where you already have the engine cards to combo the Oviraptor can add it which makes it an interaction on the turn of the opponent who plays around cards Blind Second as Dark Ruler No More.

- Another very good interaction is when the opponent uses Triple Tactic Talents and steal Tyranno and you use Doodle Beast eff to enter the field and destroy Tyranno forcing him to use an effect that you can negate with Dolkka and avoid losing your field for opponent's account go into the battle phase with the Ultimate Conductor Tyranno.

- In the match against Floowandereeze you can use him to get rid of Wind Barrier Statue since for example by Normal Summoning Oviraptor and adding him to your hand you can threaten the battle phase and if he summons Raiza you use him to tribute Oviraptor and how it comes into play by tribute summoning Wind Barrier Statue and Empen won't be a problem because you destroy Wind Barrier Statue and play smoothly.

 

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////Extra Deck Cards You Can Replace:

- The main one is Knightmare Phoenix but in the current format of Tearlaments there are several decks using Field Spell Floodgates like Necrovalley or Zombie World and having access to Phoenix is very good.

- The second option is PSY-Framelord Omega but it is very important for you to have another way to return Miscellaneousaurus to the GY.

- Because of Spright Elf Petiteranodon becomes an insane card in the deck because you always manage to Reborn it back to the field and that way Tyranno destroys it and you bring Pankratops to be another interruption against the opponent. So always try to access it in combos so that this interaction is possible.

Another very important detail to note in Spright Elf is that in cases where you do Linkuriboh + I:P Masquerena you can transform both into Spright Elf and Reborn from Petiteranodon and on the opponent's turn you can Reborn from I:P Masquerena again when he summons a monster to the field then you can destroy Petiteranodon with Tyranno and bring Pankratops from the deck and with I:P Masquerena make Unicorn to bounce another card. That is, you can transform the Spright Elf in two interactions on the opponent's turn to destroy and shuffle cards back to the deck.

 

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Finally, a very important detail is related to the field spell Magical Mid-Breaker Field because it manages to protect you from the target of cards and destruction in your Normal Summon or in your Ogdoadic monsters which is very good going first or second.

- The main detail about the card is that it can only be activated at the start of Main Phase 1 or Main Phase 2 just like the Pot of Extravagance card works. So remember that if you are going to use Set Rotation to set it on your side of the field you must activate Set Rotation in the Standby Phase and start your Main Phase 1 by activating it.

- Another important fact about the card is that it doesn't allow you to activate or set another Field Spell which can be an excellent interaction against Floowandereeze and anti-meta decks that use Floodgates like Necrovalley and Zombie World as a Pendulum and Crystal Beast deck for example . With Magical Mid-Breaker Field on the opponent's side, he can't activate another Field Spell until he manages to get rid of it.

 

///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

A curiosity is that the Dinosaur deck was not made to use Extra Deck so as the Main Deck manages to turn around very well, in the past you never had good options of LINK-2 Monsters at your disposal but now with time the Scrap engine with the insane Scrap Wyvern on hand and now we have Spright Elf which is also an absurd strong card that brings several benefits including the main one of allowing you to continue to destroy Babycerasaurus every turn to generate advantage.

Among direct and indirect supports I can mention several examples: Animadorned Archosaur, Dinowrestler Pankratops, Scrap Raptor, Doodle Beast - Tyranno, Scrap Wyvern and Spright Elf.

In this way, this deck reached a point where I see that it already has so many main deck and extra deck improvements that I don't complain at all about future supports. Of course, being extremely generic for Dinosaur-type monsters will always be a problem for Konami to create cards of this type of monster without this deck taking advantage. I think the main factor behind the latest indirect supports were actually made on purpose by Konami, now all that's missing is a good Dinosaur-type Extra Deck monster since the existing ones are specific or don't help the deck itself.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////

deck_excerpt: Orcust, 3-Axis, Burning Abyss, Phantom Knight, Pain
deck_description:
As of this deck's submission, it is my first day of Domain Format, so there are many ways in which this deck can be improved, optimized, and overall made to be more focused.

This list aims to abuse 3 things that I found would be crazy when looking at the format:

1. Invoked Elysium as a Deck Master (Also Five-Headed Dragon and Link-Dragon to an extent), as they allow you to bypass one of the bigger limitations of the format: The monsters available for you to use, as Invoked Elysium's domain is absolute- you are allowed yo use any monster on an Elysium deck.

2. The forbidden/limited list, being as of right now, is completely empty. This means that along with DM Elysium, you are functionally playing a Highlander deck on the Traditional list, which means that there are many ways to break it.

3. The 3-axis engine, along with the orcust/knightmare package, which are both completely legal right now due to the conditions I mentioned above. Although it may not be the most effective way to use the orcust line on a Domain deck, I am both very new here, and very lazy, so I just put the cards that make funny cherubini together and hoped that the most effortless way to put material on board would be enough (which it might be, but probably isn't).

All in all, this deck is mostly a proof of concept that aims to show how stupid easy it is to jam orcusts in any deck that doesn't mind running Elysium as the DM, and how consistent it can be besides the clause that limits every card in the pool (i'm not even running Girsu lmao), so here are my final observations.

Invoked Elysium is an absurdly strong Deck Master, and it might allow even crazier stuff than what i'm showing right here (Also partially applies to Five-Headed Dragon and Link-Dragon).

Knightmare Mermaid is a total bore of a card that can allow any half consistent deck in the format to artificially up it's ceilling by a decent ammount. 

Better builds of this deck could probably run Summon Sorceress to summon Girsu, the Orcust Mekk-Knight from the deck, but I am not a good enough deck builder to apply that right now.

Number 86: Heroic Champion - Rhongomyniad is a completely legal route you could take with this engine, and in the case of a possible Elysium ban would still work with the Dragons, as you do not need any light monsters to make a deck that can bring him out (Foxy Tune is the only LIGHT in this list).

Predaplant Verte Anaconda is mermaid but for any DARK deck.

Imperial Order and Royal Oppression 's only downside in a 60 card deck is getting beat up IRL by the people you are playing with (or in game if they all decide to focus your floodgating ass.



That's about it, thanks for reading if you did, ask any questions if you may have any doubts, and thanks a lot to ItThatBetrayed4026  and DivinityKing for helping me get used to the rules of the format, and to Quilpreal and loubob for being cool to talk to.

deck_excerpt: OTK, Gren Maju, You're in Danger!
deck_description:
Welcome to my newly updated Gren Maju Danger build reflecting the latest banlist, as well as the expected decks that could make an appearance.

There have been numerous changes to the main deck. D-Shifter has been relegated back to the side deck as I expect Kashtira to be a prominent matchup, plus with Bystials being likely to feature as well, having too many darks in the deck is less ideal that in was before. In it's place I have opted for Lava Golem, as not only does it synergise with Trade-In, it also allows me to remove Arise-Heart and another monster from the Kashtira end board, plus other troublesome boards created by Bystial D-Link/Branded. Now that Barrier Statue Of The Stormwinds has been banned, I have replaced Gardarla with Gamecial. Gamecial does the same thing as Gardarla did, but with 500 less attack points, so the likes of Gizemek/Pankratops can now run over it if neccessary. Panktratops has now made a return to the main deck after a few formats away, due to destruction not being particularly effective. Ultimate Slayer has returned as my main weapon of choice going blind. It's effect allows me to remove Arise-Heart and other troublesome cards such as Apolussa, Borellend, Baronne, Masquerade/Mirrorjade e.t.c whilst also gaining additional benefits from the dumped monsters. Triple Tactics Thrust was added as it is particularly useful for adding a card such as Ultimate Slayer to hand due to Shangri-Ira activating during the standby phase, as is also effective when going 1st against opposing Handtraps/Bystial activations e.t.c. to search for floodgates post side.

The deck's function is basically the same as always. Attempt to OTK and if not end of 4 material Zeus and hope your opponent can't break through. 

The extra deck consists mainly of Slayer targets, powerful XYZ's monsters and some generic utility link monsters. Mereologic is extremely good paired with Slayer. Not only can you remove Arise Heart, you can also negate the effects of the monster Shangri-Ira summons during the Standby (Fenrir/Unicorn). 

The side deck features Shifter, to hurt every single graveyard reliant strategy in existence. Heat Wave basically just says "you can't summon", so i'll more than likely OTK you on my next turn. Twin Twisters because i expect some form of backrow to feature in most decks and the usual floodgates of Dimensional Barrier and There Can Be Only One are fairly self-explainatory.

Insect Swarming + Control.

GENERAL TIPS

+ Parasite Paracide turns ALL your opponent's monsters into Insects while on their field by its effect--it will COMPLETELY shut down their ability to attack with Insect Barrier in play. Set them up to get stuck in this position once Parasite Paracide is placed into their deck by playing Jade Insect Whistle right before ending your turn.

+ With Parasite Paracide in play, it as well as all other monsters on the opponent's field will count toward powering up Insect Queen.

+ Insect Imitation can turn a Needle Worm or Drill Bug into a Dream Cicada, Warm Worm, Fairyant the Circula Sorcerer, Howling Insect, Infinite Antlion, or Beetrooper Scale Bomber from the deck once it has fulfilled its single, one-use effect to avoid its low-stats liability.

+ Beetrooper Armor Horn's effect to normal summon a monster allows you to then immediately go into Seraphim Papillion.

+ Resonance Insect is a perfect target for Infinite Antlion's on-summon effect, as its own effect activates upon being sent from the field to the GY.

+ Cocoon of Ultra Evolution allows you to tribute 1 Insect w/ an equipped card from EITHER field; Parasite Paranoid can equip to any monster & makes them Insect-type, all on its own.

+ Contact "C" is a way to force an Insect monster on the opponent's field, which can't attack you while Insect Barrier is active, and will also keep them from Extra Deck summoning if they are not able to use it as summoning material.

+ The tokens summoned from Worm Bait, Multiplication of Ants, Beetrooper Decent, or Beetrooper Squad can be used as tribute fodder for Insect Queen and Metamorphosed Insect Queen's effects (Army Ant Token is viable; it is only discluded from being tributed specifically for a tribute *summon*).

+ As none of them require effect or non-token monsters specifically as material, the tokens can be used as Extra Deck summoning material. 

+ With Bug Matrix in effect, you can repeatedly stack material into Number 20: Giga-Brilliant to use its full-field ATK gain effect more than just twice.

+ If just one monster equipped with Parasite Paranoid is on the opponent's field, or if Parasite Paracide is on their field, you can activate Rivalry of Warlords to trap them into only being able to add more Insects to their monster zones, or stop them from being able to summon entirely if they have no Insects in their own deck, unless/until Rivalry of Warlords is negated or removed from the field.

+ If you're looking to go for the Kaijus, make sure it's Kumongous, the Sticky String Kaiju (2400 ATK) you give to the opponent, so you can can put Gadarla, the Mystery Dust Kaiju (2700 ATK) on your own field.

deck_description: Machines

So the banlist happened.... and Barrier Statue was taken away from the deck. Many people think that the deck is done as it's main win con is no longer available. Also, Kashtira easily plays around the secondary win con of the deck, D-Shifter with ease. They are wrong. Statue while strong, was at times just one big target. And D-Shifter is no longer needed in the main deck as Kashtira will likely rise to be the top deck of the format. This allows the deck room to now synergize more effectively with an engine that doesn't require the extra deck, and uses it for interruption and advantage. That engine, is Dogmatika...

The loss of Statue and relegation of Shifter to the side is more than made up for by the increase in main deck interruptions you can field. Nadir is both used to add/recycle Ecclesia, and also dump extra deck monsters that can either disrupt the opponent or gain further advantage. Ultimate Slayer removes most problematic boss monsters whilst also being able to dump ED monsters like Nadir for further uses. Slayer also has the added benefits of not being able to be stopped by monster negates. Evenly is also an incredibly strong card against many decks as well.Triple Tactics Talent/Thrust are self explainatory. Scary Sea has been added because Kashtira will be hard pressed to put anything of note up without having Kashtira Birth in hand. The rest of the deck is fairly standard, but instead of the usual end board of Empen, Statue and Dreaming Town/Map, you aim to have Empen, Ecclessia, Punishment and either Dreaming Town/Scary Sea depending on the deck you are up against.

Nothing of note really needs to be said about the Extra Deck except it's tailored to make best use of Ultimate Slayer and Nadir Servant. N'Tss/Garura provide extra disruption and advantage against fusion based strategies. Wind Pegasus and Omega offer disruption or recovering assests from the grave, as well as removing troublesome Synchro monsters. Mereologic is very strong to not only remove a key XYZ's monster (Arise-Heart), as well as negating another monster effect on the field (usually Unicorn). Zeus package never used but still useful and Tri-Brigade Omen/Ferrijit to add more monsters and fix hands, as well as  helping to remove links such as Apolussa.

For the side deck. D-Shifter is purely for decks not named Kashtira/mirrors. An extra copy of Scary Sea and Unxplored Winds for greater chance of stopping Kashtira going 1st and board breaking going second. Harpie's purely because it's generically good against backrow. Solemn and Harpie's Feather Storm for floodgating your opponent or stopping potentially crushing cards and Eclipse mainly for Kashtira but may swap with Lightning Storm for more generic scenarios.

deck_description:
Welcome to another one my machination, feudal Japan fit robots join forces with samurais and modern construction equipment to defeat bigger foes!

Part 1: Gold dusted gears (Karakuri)

Karakuri is an archetype of Earth Machines focused on battle position modulation, but here we are using them for their access to certain levels for synchro summons...

  • Karakuri Merchant mdl 177 "Inashichi" - Is a non-opt search for your entire archetype upon normal summon, he is searcheable by other cards in the Deck, arguably the most important card in the Deck.
  • Karakuri Komachi mdl 224 "Ninishi" - Helps normal summoning other Inashichis from your Hand but just like Karakuri Barrel mdl 96 "Shinkuro" , Karakuri Gama mdl 4624 "Shirokunishi" and Karakuri Watchdog mdl 313 "Saizan" you are mostly using them as Tuners to get to your high level Synchros.
  • Karakuri Bonze mdl 9763 "Kunamzan" - Can special summon itself as a Tuner, but you are using him as a level 5 material for Infinitrack River Stormer , his special summon does unfortunately lock you into Earth Machines.
  • Karakuri Cash Cache and Karakuri Cash Inn : Cache is your non-opt ROTA and Cash is your negate.
  • Karakuri Shogun mdl 00 "Burei" , Karakuri Steel Shogun mdl 00X "Bureido" and Karakuri Super Shogun mdl 00N "Bureibu" : Respectively a level 7, 8 and 9, all of them share the effect of summoning any Karakuri from your Deck... which helps you go crazy with your Synchros or Xyzs. The only other notable thing is Karakuri Gama mdl 4624 "Shirokunishi" and Inn causes Bureido to draw and Bureibu to banish a card your opponent controls.

Part 2: Other Earth Machines

  • Superheavy Samurai Prodigy Wakaushi , Superheavy Samurai Monk Warrior Big Benkei , Superheavy Samurai Soulgaia Booster and Superheavy Samurai Bike - Wakaushi is just insane, it summons itself and puts Benkei on the scales searching Gaia which special summons itself making a level 8 Synchro meaning you can make Karakuri Steel Shogun mdl 00X "Bureido" which can summon Karakuri Barrel mdl 96 "Shinkuro" to go into Baronne de Fleur , you can summon something else to make Karakuri Shogun mdl 00 "Burei" which summons Karakuri Gama mdl 4624 "Shirokunishi" to make Crystal Wing Synchro Dragon or help making Naturia Beast , besides that you get a free 1-8 scale. Bike helps searching the engine but you cannot under any circumstance use S/T before doing it or else you won't be able to use it.
  • Therion "King" Regulus - Searcheable negate via Infinitrack River Stormer .
  • Heavy Forward , Infinitrack Brutal Dozer , Infinitrack Trencher and Infinitrack Anchor Drill - Helps making your Synchros and you can avoid Dozer's lock by pendulum summoning it, anchor helps making Synchros in a pinch, trencher helps with bringing back resources and Dozer can make Stormer to go into Infinitrack Earth Slicer .
  • Infinitrack Crab Crane , Outrigger Extension , Infinitrack Goliath , Infinitrack River Stormer and Kashtira Arise-Heart - Crab can banish a Earth Machine to get outrigger, you make Goliath over Stormer and then tribute it to summon and attach itself to Stormer, target Stormer with Outrigger to summon Arise which is now protected due to Goliath's effect.
